{"cursor":"1670","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In sign language, 'location', or 'tab', refers to specific places that the hands\noccupy as they are used to form words. In Stokoe terminology it is known as the\n, an abbreviation of tabula. Location is one of five components of a sign, along\nwith handshape (), orientation (), movement (), and facial-body expression.\nDifferent sign languages make use of different locations.\n","linknr":269,"url":"Location_(sign_language)","recorded":1362665373,"links":13,"instances":["sign_language","sign_language","sign_language","sign_language"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Sign language"],"headings":["Locations in American Sign Language","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Sign_language_interpreter.jpg/160px-Sign_language_interpreter.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["handshape","sign_language"],["orientation","sign_language"],["movement","sign_language"],["expression","sign_language"]],"members":["expression","movement","orientation","handshape"],"related":["Sign_language","William_Stokoe","Handshape_(sign_language)","Orientation_(sign_language)","Movement_(sign_language)","Expression_(sign_language)","American_Sign_Language"]}